The paper deals with content-based image retrieval from large-scale remote sensing archives, which is a problem commonly addressed in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of virtual machines and cluster computing also suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the use of unsupervised ingestion processes and big data analytics implies a potential interest in machine learning (cs.LG).
